WEBVTT

00:17.475 --> 00:18.393
<i> Love,</i>

00:18.893 --> 00:21.104
<i>this is why you're not for me.</i>

00:22.647 --> 00:24.816
<i>Once upon a time, I believed in love.</i>

00:25.483 --> 00:28.319
<i>Sure, I'd been hurt before,</i>
<i>but I'd learned from that,</i>

00:28.403 --> 00:30.822
<i>and I wanted to fight for a fresh start.</i>

00:31.281 --> 00:33.241
<i>The real thing this time.</i>

00:34.284 --> 00:35.702
<i>So, boy meets girl,</i>

00:35.785 --> 00:38.121
<i>boy knows this is a something special,</i>
<i>and he thinks,</i>

00:38.204 --> 00:42.083
<i>"Let me do everything I can</i>
<i>to make this right."</i>

00:43.209 --> 00:45.170
<i>So, I did.</i>

00:48.006 --> 00:49.090
<i> I was brave.</i>

00:49.507 --> 00:50.759
<i>I was vulnerable.</i>

00:51.634 --> 00:53.428
<i>I won her the old-fashioned way.</i>

00:55.346 --> 00:57.557
<i>I tried to do everything right</i>

00:58.308 --> 00:59.309
<i>for her.</i>

00:59.809 --> 01:02.479
<i>I knew you have to do anything for love.</i>

01:03.354 --> 01:04.314
<i>So I did.</i>

01:05.440 --> 01:06.941
<i>I did whatever I had to,</i>

01:07.025 --> 01:08.443
<i>whatever it took.</i>

01:09.069 --> 01:10.737
I love you, Joe.

01:11.071 --> 01:12.238
I love you too.

01:12.655 --> 01:14.783
I heard about you and Candace.

01:15.283 --> 01:16.868
You know, I thought we were pretty happy,

01:16.951 --> 01:18.703
but she thought she could
be happier with...

01:19.579 --> 01:20.747
some guy in Rome, so...

01:20.830 --> 01:23.541
It's just how she left so suddenly...

01:24.084 --> 01:26.920
<i> But she did not trust me.</i>

01:27.420 --> 01:30.256
<i>So she started asking questions</i>
<i>about the past.</i>

01:30.340 --> 01:31.174
<i>Candace?</i>

01:31.257 --> 01:33.259
I think they dated.

01:34.219 --> 01:35.053
Oh, they did.

01:35.136 --> 01:37.722
<i>But I can't say I was shocked</i>
<i>when it didn't work out.</i>

01:37.806 --> 01:39.057
Who's Elijah?

01:40.266 --> 01:41.518
Give me my phone, Joe.

01:41.601 --> 01:44.395
-<i> He's not your brother, I know that.</i>
<i>-</i> <i>I don't love you.</i>

01:44.562 --> 01:45.396
I never have.

01:48.024 --> 01:51.402
<i> She started digging for stuff</i>
<i>that should have stayed buried.</i>

01:53.738 --> 01:54.739
<i>I picked wrong.</i>

01:55.198 --> 01:56.241
<i>I made mistakes.</i>

01:58.660 --> 02:00.120
<i>Love had made me blind.</i>

02:00.203 --> 02:01.037
<i> Joe!</i>

02:01.121 --> 02:01.996
<i>And now...</i>

02:02.080 --> 02:02.956
Joe!

02:03.039 --> 02:04.582
<i>...love turned to poison.</i>

02:04.666 --> 02:06.042
<i> Tell me I'm crazy.</i>

02:07.127 --> 02:08.378
Tell me you didn't...

02:09.379 --> 02:10.922
kill Peach.

02:13.299 --> 02:15.385
Tell me you didn't kill Peach.

02:16.469 --> 02:20.223
<i> And when love dies, it really hurts.</i>

02:20.598 --> 02:22.517
<i>-The bottom line is...</i>

02:24.644 --> 02:25.854
<i>she couldn't love me back.</i>

02:30.233 --> 02:31.568
<i>And our love died.</i>

02:32.026 --> 02:33.236
<i>I thought that was the end.</i>

02:34.112 --> 02:35.280
<i>A sad story.</i>

02:37.073 --> 02:40.034
<i>A broken heart I'd have to heal from</i>
<i>to love again.</i>

02:41.327 --> 02:44.414
<i>But no, there was more hurt in store.</i>

02:48.334 --> 02:49.169
Candace.

02:49.252 --> 02:52.172
I think we have some unfinished business
to talk about.

02:53.006 --> 02:53.882
Yeah.

02:54.757 --> 02:56.885
<i> And so I realize this is what I get</i>

02:57.510 --> 02:58.887
<i>for trying so hard.</i>

02:58.970 --> 02:59.971
<i>I can't love again.</i>

03:00.388 --> 03:03.099
<i>I can't risk it. It's too dangerous.</i>

03:03.850 --> 03:06.394
<i>The only fresh start is a start</i>

03:06.853 --> 03:07.854
<i>without love.</i>

03:07.937 --> 03:08.855
Cut!

03:08.938 --> 03:11.900
We're gonna go again from the top.
Quickly.

03:12.775 --> 03:13.610
Nice.

03:14.277 --> 03:16.404
Print that.
We're gonna go again from the top.

03:16.779 --> 03:17.697
<i> This...</i>

03:18.198 --> 03:19.699
<i>is what it's come to.</i>

03:24.454 --> 03:25.955
<i>♪ I'm a troubled man ♪</i>

03:26.039 --> 03:28.208
<i>♪ Changed by the things I do ♪</i>

03:28.333 --> 03:30.335
♪<i> True, but it's funny how </i>♪

03:31.461 --> 03:34.130
<i> Love has taken me to dark places.</i>

03:35.882 --> 03:37.508
<i>But Los Angeles...</i>

03:38.635 --> 03:40.803
<i>has gotta be as dark as it gets.</i>

03:42.013 --> 03:44.474
<i>When you're running from someone</i>
<i>who thinks they know you,</i>

03:44.849 --> 03:47.101
<i>the best place to hide</i>
<i>is a city they think you hate</i>

03:47.393 --> 03:49.062
<i>because, well, I do.</i>

03:49.145 --> 03:50.271
Hi, gorgeous people!

03:50.355 --> 03:52.148
Just wanna say thank you. Wow.

03:52.232 --> 03:53.650
Three million followers?

03:54.317 --> 03:57.320
I'm honestly choked up
thinking about how much I love each...

03:57.403 --> 04:01.032
<i> I'm closing my heart,</i>
<i>like an out-of-business bookstore,</i>

04:01.115 --> 04:03.910
<i>and I'm here for the moment</i>
<i>where everyone is too into themselves</i>

04:03.993 --> 04:05.453
<i>to ever connect with another person.</i>

04:05.536 --> 04:08.039
<i>It's the worst city in the world</i>
<i>and the last place I wanna be,</i>

04:08.122 --> 04:09.290
<i>and that's perfect.</i>

04:09.999 --> 04:10.917
<i>It's temporary.</i>

04:11.209 --> 04:15.129
<i>Regroup, get some cash together,</i>
<i>figure out next moves, go.</i>

04:15.672 --> 04:17.090
<i>Never look back.</i>

04:17.173 --> 04:19.550
<i>It's a chance to get back</i>
<i>to who I really am:</i>

04:20.176 --> 04:21.970
<i>-a quiet guy...</i>

04:22.220 --> 04:24.514
<i>...who just wants to lead a quiet life.</i>

04:32.772 --> 04:35.149
<i> I've done time in uglier cages.</i>

04:36.234 --> 04:37.777
Welcome. I'm Delilah.

04:38.194 --> 04:39.654
Will Bettelheim. Nice to meet you.

04:39.737 --> 04:41.364
Your credit came back sparkling, Will.

04:41.447 --> 04:42.490
Oh, good, good.

04:42.573 --> 04:44.617
But I looked you up.
You're not on the socials.

04:44.701 --> 04:46.244
Like, at all.

04:46.327 --> 04:48.329
Thought you might be some kind of freak.

04:48.579 --> 04:51.082
Just not great
at keeping up with that stuff.

04:51.165 --> 04:54.127
Do you not keep up
with brushing your teeth?

04:54.711 --> 04:56.921
I'm kidding,
I'm kidding. Okay.

04:57.005 --> 04:59.590
I just have this vacancy
on the first floor.

04:59.674 --> 05:02.468
-Do you wanna see it? It's bigger.
-I like the second floor.

05:02.885 --> 05:03.720
It's quieter.

05:04.053 --> 05:04.971
All right.

05:05.596 --> 05:07.432
So rent's due on the third,

05:07.807 --> 05:09.934
No loud music after ten.

05:10.810 --> 05:12.020
Two pet limit.

05:12.103 --> 05:15.732
And don't cook meth in your kitchen.

05:15.815 --> 05:16.858
You got it.

05:20.445 --> 05:22.989
You can keep the furniture if you want
or just let me know

05:23.072 --> 05:24.490
and we can have someone take it out.

05:25.033 --> 05:27.952
The last tenant
kind of left in a hurry, so...

05:28.661 --> 05:30.747
hopefully it'll be better luck for you.

05:31.497 --> 05:34.167
I'm in number one if you need anything.

05:34.625 --> 05:35.585
That sounds great.

05:36.127 --> 05:38.504
All right. See ya.

05:44.469 --> 05:46.804
<i> Home sweet prison.</i>

05:54.812 --> 05:57.148
<i>It's uncomfortable, all of this.</i>

05:58.066 --> 05:59.692
<i>But that's good, I'm detoxing.</i>

06:00.234 --> 06:01.778
<i>Detox should be uncomfortable.</i>

06:02.362 --> 06:04.072
<i>I've left so much behind.</i>

06:05.114 --> 06:08.034
<i>And I know there's a side of me</i>

06:08.117 --> 06:09.619
<i>that I let get out of control,</i>

06:09.702 --> 06:12.789
<i>and now controlling</i> <i>is everything.</i>

06:12.872 --> 06:14.457
<i>But, that said,</i>

06:14.540 --> 06:16.376
<i>cold turkey leads to rebound,</i>

06:16.459 --> 06:17.710
<i>leads to heartbreak,</i>

06:17.794 --> 06:19.212
<i>if not crime scenes,</i>

06:19.295 --> 06:21.964
<i>and posthumous best sellers.</i>

06:23.132 --> 06:24.592
<i>Addiction management is key.</i>

06:25.551 --> 06:26.594
<i>Ten minutes a day.</i>

06:26.677 --> 06:28.721
<i>Do not fixate on any one person.</i>

06:28.805 --> 06:30.765
<i>Do not get involved,</i>
<i>do not even look them up,</i>

06:30.848 --> 06:33.768
<i>because I know I can get swept up.</i>

06:33.851 --> 06:35.853
<i>-But that's not happening.</i>

06:36.771 --> 06:38.731
<i>This is a fresh start.</i>

06:47.615 --> 06:48.866
<i>In my dreams...</i>

06:49.450 --> 06:50.368
<i>Beck's alive.</i>

06:51.411 --> 06:53.538
<i>She forgives me for everything I did.</i>

06:53.621 --> 06:55.998
<i>She apologizes for everything she did.</i>

06:56.332 --> 06:58.042
<i>And she says, "Don't worry,</i>

06:58.126 --> 06:59.168
<i>Candace is gone.</i>

07:00.253 --> 07:01.295
<i>Forever."</i>

07:02.213 --> 07:03.548
<i>But then I wake up...</i>

07:04.257 --> 07:05.341
<i>and remember.</i>

07:06.426 --> 07:09.178
I think we have
some unfinished business to talk about.

07:09.262 --> 07:10.263
Okay.

07:10.847 --> 07:12.932
Okay, let's go somewhere

07:13.349 --> 07:15.560
and we can sit and talk.

07:15.852 --> 07:17.562
As long as it's nice...

07:17.979 --> 07:19.147
and public.

07:26.028 --> 07:27.572
Are you gonna tell me what you want?

07:27.655 --> 07:29.198
I'm craving French fries.

07:29.699 --> 07:30.533
Candace--

07:30.616 --> 07:33.786
-Hi. What can I get for you?
-Fries, please, a side of ranch.

07:34.370 --> 07:35.788
Vanilla milkshake.

07:36.164 --> 07:37.248
You want anything, bunny?

07:38.458 --> 07:40.293
-No.
- Okay.

07:40.585 --> 07:41.627
I'll be right back.

07:45.423 --> 07:48.092
I want you to know I want it to stay gone.

07:48.551 --> 07:49.969
I mean, you sure thought I was dead

07:50.052 --> 07:51.888
or you wouldn't have
just left me there, right?

07:52.013 --> 07:54.432
I was prepared to count my blessings
and never come back.

07:54.515 --> 07:55.850
That's not how any of it happened.

07:55.933 --> 07:57.685
So, anyways, there I am,

07:58.186 --> 07:59.312
in a new town,

07:59.770 --> 08:01.063
a new girl,

08:02.148 --> 08:03.649
and I walk into this store,

08:04.108 --> 08:05.485
and there's this book...

08:06.569 --> 08:08.988
by a woman named Guinevere...

08:10.364 --> 08:11.199
Beck.

08:14.160 --> 08:16.412
You did it again, didn't you?

08:18.247 --> 08:19.999
What do you want, Candace?

08:21.292 --> 08:24.545
To kill you with my bare hands.

08:26.672 --> 08:27.757
I'm kidding.

08:28.716 --> 08:29.800
I could never.

08:31.010 --> 08:35.014
I'm gonna go to the cops,
and I'm gonna tell them everything.

08:36.974 --> 08:38.643
Nope, sorry, not that either.

08:39.810 --> 08:40.978
Too easy on you.

08:51.781 --> 08:52.782
<i> People.</i>

08:52.865 --> 08:54.367
<i>People are predictable.</i>

08:54.450 --> 08:56.285
<i>I cannot afford to be predictable.</i>

08:56.619 --> 08:58.287
<i>My life depends on that.</i>

08:59.038 --> 09:01.666
<i>But love, love is what kept me open,</i>

09:01.749 --> 09:04.669
<i>alive, different, real.</i>

09:04.961 --> 09:08.214
<i>And I also can't afford to do love,</i>
<i>so you see my dilemma.</i>

09:08.297 --> 09:10.216
<i>Lady, how many photos does it take?</i>
<i>Come on.</i>

09:10.299 --> 09:12.552
Are you like, "Lady, come on.

09:12.635 --> 09:13.970
How many photos does it take?"

09:14.720 --> 09:17.390
Crazy thing is,
she never posts any of them.

09:17.932 --> 09:20.101
That's, like, gotta be a diagnosis, right?

09:20.351 --> 09:23.145
<i> Precocious, unsupervised kid</i>
<i>who thinks she's not a kid.</i>

09:23.229 --> 09:25.398
Ms. Strauss secretly has six chihuahuas

09:25.481 --> 09:26.941
so she walks them in shifts.

09:27.525 --> 09:28.568
And you?

09:29.527 --> 09:31.529
You are Will Bettelheim,

09:32.071 --> 09:32.905
LA newbie.

09:33.155 --> 09:34.448
Yeah, that's me.

09:34.532 --> 09:35.866
<i> Who is protecting her?</i>

09:35.950 --> 09:37.994
<i>No, no, she is not my problem.</i>

09:38.077 --> 09:38.911
What's your Insta?

09:39.745 --> 09:41.038
Or do you only have a Finsta?

09:41.330 --> 09:43.040
-I'm a little behind the times.
-Clearly.

09:43.916 --> 09:46.252
Anyway, I'm @Ellie-Eyeballs.

09:48.754 --> 09:49.630
So...

09:50.423 --> 09:51.424
you have a girlfriend yet?

09:51.507 --> 09:52.967
<i> Holy shit.</i>

09:53.050 --> 09:54.719
Ellie, how old are you? Like 14?

09:55.011 --> 09:55.970
Fifteen.

09:56.262 --> 09:58.097
Basically 16, so...

09:58.556 --> 10:00.725
<i></i>
<i>No, she's not my problem.</i>

10:01.100 --> 10:02.101
It was nice to meet you.

10:02.393 --> 10:03.352
Cool.

10:04.145 --> 10:05.062
Manners.

10:05.146 --> 10:06.814
Thank you so much for stopping by.

10:06.897 --> 10:08.941
I appreciate being the first call.

10:09.025 --> 10:11.235
So Delilah, she's not a hooker.

10:11.986 --> 10:13.279
It's what you're thinking, right?

10:14.030 --> 10:15.823
Yeah, no, she's a reporter,

10:15.906 --> 10:16.991
that guy's a publicist,

10:17.074 --> 10:21.120
and he just paid some crazy kill fee to
not run something about someone famous.

10:21.454 --> 10:23.247
-It's sick, she's a genius.
- Ellie?

10:23.581 --> 10:25.124
No harassing the tenants.

10:25.207 --> 10:26.876
I'm not. We're old friends.

10:26.959 --> 10:28.753
Well, you're late for school, smart-ass.

10:29.045 --> 10:30.588
<i> Too young to be Ellie's mom.</i>

10:30.880 --> 10:33.090
Is that my shirt? That's my fucking shirt.

10:33.174 --> 10:35.217
-How many times...?
-<i> Sisters.</i>

10:35.301 --> 10:38.721
Can you please not wear that to school
and destroy it, please?

10:39.013 --> 10:41.015
<i> If Delilah counts</i>
<i>as parental supervision,</i>

10:41.432 --> 10:43.976
<i>-it explains everything.</i>
<i>-</i>It looks hotter on me, though.

10:44.310 --> 10:46.729
Cool story. Any day now.

10:46.812 --> 10:49.732
<i> Note to self: steer clear</i>
<i>of their entire red flag galaxy.</i>

10:49.815 --> 10:50.691
Hey.

10:53.194 --> 10:54.820
You lay a finger on her,

10:54.904 --> 10:57.657
and I will vivisect
your individual scrotums.

10:57.948 --> 10:59.033
She's a kid.

11:03.746 --> 11:04.830
<i> In Los Angeles,</i>

11:05.206 --> 11:07.875
<i>grocery stores aren't just a place</i>
<i>you buy carrots,</i>

11:07.958 --> 11:10.878
<i>they're a pristine, non-GMO Disneyland,</i>

11:10.961 --> 11:13.339
<i>and king among these is Anavrin.</i>

11:13.422 --> 11:14.674
<i>Come for the spring lettuce mix,</i>

11:15.132 --> 11:16.842
<i>stay for the perfect life</i>
<i>that could be yours</i>

11:16.926 --> 11:19.512
<i>if you spend enough</i>
<i>and quit gluten, you fucking asshole.</i>

11:20.262 --> 11:23.307
<i>And yeah, obviously, Anavrin is--</i>
<i>wait for it--</i>

11:23.891 --> 11:25.559
<i>"nirvana" spelled backwards.</i>

11:26.602 --> 11:30.272
So, no experience at all in sorting
or bagging perishables?

11:31.565 --> 11:33.234
Well, I'm a quick study.

11:35.611 --> 11:37.029
It's a coveted job.

11:37.113 --> 11:39.532
Yeah, all the casting directors shop here.

11:39.615 --> 11:41.492
-So--
-Oh, I'm not an actor.

11:42.785 --> 11:44.995
Okay, let me xerox some photo ID

11:45.079 --> 11:47.289
and I'll call you ASAP
and I'll let you know.

11:47.373 --> 11:49.083
Sure thing, ID.

11:51.669 --> 11:52.586
Damn.

11:53.045 --> 11:55.923
-I know-- I know I brought it. I just...
-Are you reading that?

11:56.424 --> 11:57.466
Re-reading.

11:57.550 --> 12:00.177
It feels like it gets
more relevant every day, right?

12:00.261 --> 12:02.346
How... so?

12:03.222 --> 12:06.350
Oh, this guy's struggle trying
to get past his mistakes, you know?

12:06.726 --> 12:09.228
I don't like to get political,
but I will say

12:09.311 --> 12:11.814
our world is done for
if we don't think about that.

12:12.398 --> 12:13.441
How to be better.

12:14.066 --> 12:16.485
-I can't believe you just did that.
-Did...?

12:16.944 --> 12:20.030
Made a Russian novel
sound like something I'd <i>want </i>to read.

12:22.241 --> 12:24.452
Uh, I don't mean to spring this on you...

12:24.994 --> 12:26.871
Ever thought about working in a bookstore?

12:30.207 --> 12:33.252
We've been having a time moving product.

12:33.919 --> 12:36.380
You know, I thought
with this whole hacking democracy thing,

12:36.464 --> 12:39.133
people would be like,
"Yeah, I wanna read some Russian stuff.

12:39.216 --> 12:40.551
What's up with that place?" But...

12:41.635 --> 12:42.928
they're intimidated, you know?

12:43.220 --> 12:45.514
Hm, there's nothing to be intimidated by.

12:46.140 --> 12:48.601
It's human experience. It's universal.

12:49.310 --> 12:53.105
<i> I think I just felt my soul</i>
<i>come back into my body.</i>

12:53.189 --> 12:54.023
I love it.

12:54.106 --> 12:55.357
You sound like such a...

12:55.983 --> 12:56.942
a reader.

12:57.943 --> 12:59.945
Maybe it's 'cause
it's my favorite thing to do.

13:00.279 --> 13:01.405
That...

13:01.489 --> 13:02.323
and...

13:03.032 --> 13:04.992
recommending the perfect book.

13:05.075 --> 13:06.243
Can you start tomorrow?

13:07.953 --> 13:10.372
- Yeah.
-Perfect. Let's get you an apron.

13:10.706 --> 13:11.916
<i> A new apron?</i>

13:12.416 --> 13:13.250
<i>Joy.</i>

13:26.347 --> 13:27.306
<i> Hello...</i>

13:27.723 --> 13:28.599
<i>you.</i>

13:28.682 --> 13:30.851
<i>No, fuck, no, I'm not doing that.</i>

13:30.935 --> 13:33.562
<i>I'm not gonna try to figure out</i>
<i>who you are,</i>

13:33.646 --> 13:35.731
<i>why you look so concerned</i>

13:35.815 --> 13:38.442
<i>about the state of that heirloom tomato.</i>

13:41.904 --> 13:44.114
-Oh, did I get you? Are you okay?
-It's okay.

13:44.198 --> 13:45.950
<i> You have a way with people.</i>

13:47.576 --> 13:48.661
<i>They just like you.</i>

13:49.495 --> 13:52.331
<i>Your shirt is faded, but fresh.</i>

13:53.624 --> 13:55.251
<i>You like to take care of things.</i>

13:55.626 --> 13:58.546
<i>Your shoes are clean, but more.</i>

13:58.629 --> 14:00.965
<i>You walk in a town where nobody walks.</i>

