31:18.960 --> 31:21.004
<i>when you stop running for one second.</i>

31:21.462 --> 31:23.506
<i>I just want to stop running, Love.</i>

31:24.424 --> 31:25.592
<i>I want a home.</i>

31:34.142 --> 31:34.976
Mom?

31:37.020 --> 31:37.979
Mommy?

31:38.563 --> 31:39.606
-Mommy?
- Joe!

31:39.898 --> 31:40.940
Baby.

31:41.858 --> 31:42.817
Right here.

31:43.651 --> 31:45.111
I was afraid you left.

31:46.779 --> 31:48.406
I went to get sunscreen.

31:48.907 --> 31:49.824
Come here.

31:59.417 --> 32:00.585
It's nice here, right?

32:01.085 --> 32:03.212
We should come here every summer.

32:03.296 --> 32:05.757
It could be our home away from home.

32:07.508 --> 32:08.343
You are home.

32:08.927 --> 32:10.386
Sure, we're home.

32:10.470 --> 32:12.931
No, I mean, my home is you.

32:19.145 --> 32:20.271
Me too, Joey.

32:20.897 --> 32:21.940
Me too, you.

32:24.734 --> 32:25.777
Hey.

32:26.986 --> 32:28.488
Go get some ice cream.

32:29.697 --> 32:32.241
Then meet me back at our favorite spot.

32:32.325 --> 32:34.744
You know, the one from yesterday.
Remember?

32:35.286 --> 32:38.206
And build me a sandcastle.

32:38.289 --> 32:39.207
Okay?

32:41.876 --> 32:45.213
Mommy will be back in just a few shakes.

32:45.964 --> 32:46.881
Okay?

33:09.612 --> 33:12.115
<i> I'm an idiot.</i>

33:13.157 --> 33:15.994
<i>Did I sunburn </i>through <i>this t-shirt?</i>

33:16.077 --> 33:18.037
<i>How is that a thing?</i>

33:21.624 --> 33:24.669
<i>Worth it, all worth it, Love.</i>

33:32.218 --> 33:33.219
<i> Married.</i>

33:34.554 --> 33:35.722
<i>Married?</i>

33:49.360 --> 33:50.611
Hey, Brooklyn!

33:52.238 --> 33:53.448
I know you're in there.

33:54.282 --> 33:56.325
<i> Oh, the happily-wed missus.</i>

33:58.411 --> 33:59.370
I'm sick.

34:00.204 --> 34:02.665
You're a rookie with a sunburn
is what you are.

34:02.749 --> 34:04.167
Calvin told me at the store.

34:04.250 --> 34:05.168
Let me in.

34:08.504 --> 34:09.338
I can help.

34:13.426 --> 34:15.928
-Do you have a medical license?

34:16.095 --> 34:17.013
I'm serious, though.

34:17.096 --> 34:18.973
You didn't need to come
all the way over here.

34:19.182 --> 34:20.349
It's no problem.

34:20.892 --> 34:22.268
I live right in the neighborhood.

34:24.645 --> 34:25.855
All right.

34:27.690 --> 34:28.775
Is that salad dressing?

34:29.275 --> 34:30.485
No, it's apple cider vinegar.

34:32.487 --> 34:33.321
May I?

34:36.157 --> 34:37.492
-You want me to...?
-Yes.

34:39.535 --> 34:43.247
Trust me, in five minutes
you're going to love me for this.

34:44.749 --> 34:45.666
Smells great.

34:45.958 --> 34:47.085
Shut up.

34:52.924 --> 34:54.634
Are you okay? This must hurt.

34:57.512 --> 34:58.471
It doesn't.

35:00.306 --> 35:01.557
<i>You felt that too.</i>

35:01.974 --> 35:04.310
<i>But you're married, so you're safe.</i>

35:04.393 --> 35:06.896
<i>It's actually perfect.</i>

35:06.979 --> 35:08.189
<i>Keep it light,</i>

35:08.272 --> 35:09.148
<i>breezy.</i>

35:10.983 --> 35:12.693
There. We'll give that a minute.

35:17.406 --> 35:18.991
Okay, now I need to ask you a question

35:19.075 --> 35:21.202
that's deadly serious and deeply personal.

35:21.869 --> 35:22.703
Okay.

35:23.287 --> 35:25.039
Is that 99-cent ramen?

35:27.917 --> 35:28.793
-Yeah.
-No.

35:29.210 --> 35:30.253
-Yeah.
-No, Will, no.

35:30.336 --> 35:31.838
You're an Angeleno now.

35:31.921 --> 35:33.673
I'm not, actually.

35:33.756 --> 35:36.008
You know, you ex-New Yorkers
are the worst.

35:36.092 --> 35:39.220
I mean, haven't-- haven't you ever...
fallen in love

35:39.303 --> 35:40.596
reading Joan Didion

35:40.680 --> 35:42.181
or Raymond Chandler,

35:42.265 --> 35:43.516
or Francesca Lia Block?

35:43.599 --> 35:44.559
You know, these...

35:47.228 --> 35:49.856
-You've never read Joan fucking Didion.
- A little.

35:49.939 --> 35:52.108
-She's next.
-No, you, you're missing out, okay?

35:52.191 --> 35:53.609
This city, is...

35:53.693 --> 35:55.236
it's... it's...

35:55.319 --> 35:56.863
a million cities, it's...

35:57.155 --> 35:58.114
I mean...

36:02.160 --> 36:04.453
We're going. We're going!

36:04.537 --> 36:05.496
Where, exactly?

36:06.664 --> 36:08.749
As many places as we need to
to convert you.

36:08.958 --> 36:09.792
Come on.

36:11.419 --> 36:12.545
Let's go!

36:12.628 --> 36:14.255
-Okay.
-Come on, snob!

36:14.338 --> 36:15.715
All right, hang on a minute.

36:15.798 --> 36:16.966
Need to get my jacket.

36:20.511 --> 36:21.387
Okay.

36:22.346 --> 36:23.472
Just gotta lock up.

36:26.350 --> 36:29.061
<i> It's my favorite place in the city.</i>

36:29.812 --> 36:31.063
<i>I have this theory.</i>

36:31.147 --> 36:34.192
<i>It's not my theory, it's the late,</i>
<i>great food writer Jonathan Gold's,</i>

36:34.275 --> 36:37.403
<i>whose life mission was to know</i>
<i>Los Angeles the best way:</i>

36:37.945 --> 36:38.779
<i>through food.</i>

36:39.238 --> 36:40.656
<i>And, uh, he said,</i>

36:40.740 --> 36:43.451
<i>"There exists for each of us</i>
<i>a perfect taco."</i>

36:43.534 --> 36:44.368
<i>Point is...</i>

36:44.577 --> 36:45.536
Is it good?

36:45.620 --> 36:48.831
<i> ...we are gonna find you</i>
<i>your perfect bite.</i>

36:48.915 --> 36:50.291
-It's amazing.
-But is it perfect?

36:50.374 --> 36:51.209
It's a taco.

36:52.960 --> 36:54.795
We have more work to do. Come, let's go.

36:55.880 --> 36:57.298
Wait, hang on, this?

36:57.381 --> 36:59.800
-You're telling me--
-No, no, no. Come on, come on, please.

37:00.218 --> 37:02.511
You are going to love it.
It's going to be so worth it.

37:05.556 --> 37:06.432
Okay.

37:07.558 --> 37:08.476
Thank you.

37:10.811 --> 37:11.938
So you really didn't like it?

37:12.021 --> 37:13.981
No! No, no, no.
I would bathe in that sauce.

37:14.065 --> 37:15.149
Stop lying to me.

37:16.150 --> 37:17.360
I'll figure you out.

37:17.443 --> 37:18.736
This is science.

37:19.445 --> 37:21.155
<i>♪ Victories ♪</i>

37:21.656 --> 37:23.532
<i>♪ Look better when you've called it... ♪</i>

37:26.327 --> 37:31.040
<i>♪ Misery's the moment when I lost you ♪</i>

37:32.416 --> 37:34.627
<i>♪ It's pleasure in a costume ♪</i>

37:37.088 --> 37:38.422
Oh, so close.

37:39.548 --> 37:40.508
Inches away.

37:42.885 --> 37:43.719
Okay.

37:44.637 --> 37:45.888
Research complete.

37:46.889 --> 37:48.099
Final destination.

37:50.393 --> 37:51.227
Let's hit it!

38:16.252 --> 38:19.046
<i> Let me tell you a little bit</i>
<i>about yourself, Will Bettelheim.</i>

38:20.589 --> 38:21.799
<i>You are not a snob.</i>

38:24.093 --> 38:25.469
<i>You're just old-fashioned.</i>

38:27.430 --> 38:28.931
<i>You like things that are real,</i>

38:29.390 --> 38:31.142
<i>made right by people who care.</i>

38:31.225 --> 38:33.185
<i>You like strong flavors.</i>

38:33.269 --> 38:35.021
<i>Gimmicks don't seduce you.</i>

38:35.104 --> 38:37.273
<i>What seduces you is the real thing.</i>

38:40.151 --> 38:40.985
<i>Therefore...</i>

38:44.155 --> 38:45.114
Roast chicken.

38:45.573 --> 38:46.407
In cooking school,

38:46.490 --> 38:49.160
they used to tell us that you could
tell everything about a cook

38:49.243 --> 38:50.661
based on their roast chicken,

38:50.745 --> 38:52.246
so I became a bit obsessive.

38:52.538 --> 38:54.498
And you are gonna benefit from that.

38:54.874 --> 38:56.334
You went to cooking school?

38:56.625 --> 38:57.543
Yeah.

38:58.044 --> 38:59.086
That's a long story.

39:04.759 --> 39:05.718
<i>Voilà.</i>

39:06.969 --> 39:08.346
Okay.

39:09.555 --> 39:11.891
Make sure you have some skin and carrot...

39:12.683 --> 39:13.976
and some crispy potato...

39:14.060 --> 39:16.854
and then I'll rub it around
in the reduction a little bit.

39:20.524 --> 39:22.443
-May I eat it?
-Yes, you may eat it.

39:28.908 --> 39:30.034
<i> I get it now.</i>

39:30.951 --> 39:31.786
Well?

39:32.703 --> 39:36.123
<i> It's everything I like,</i>
<i>made exquisitely, but what's perfect...</i>

39:36.791 --> 39:38.501
<i>is you made it for me.</i>

39:38.584 --> 39:40.086
Is that you're speechless?

39:41.837 --> 39:42.922
Perfect bite?

39:46.384 --> 39:47.343
Perfect.

39:48.552 --> 39:49.637
It's perfect.

39:49.720 --> 39:50.638
Yes!

39:51.347 --> 39:52.223
I knew it.

39:52.765 --> 39:53.933
You were tough...

39:54.600 --> 39:55.476
but...

39:55.935 --> 39:57.186
I am a champion.

40:03.526 --> 40:04.360
Shit.

40:04.610 --> 40:06.487
-I'm sorry. Did I say--
-No.

40:06.904 --> 40:08.948
I have to tell you something, and...

40:09.323 --> 40:10.908
I'm just gonna come out and say it.

40:11.617 --> 40:14.328
The community garden that we walked by?

40:15.538 --> 40:16.914
I got married there...

40:17.957 --> 40:18.916
three years ago.

40:20.459 --> 40:21.419
Um...

40:21.669 --> 40:24.547
We met in school and we were young, but...

40:24.839 --> 40:25.673
I just knew--

40:25.756 --> 40:28.008
-I'm sorry if I sent the wrong signal--
-No, he's dead.

40:30.970 --> 40:32.972
Yeah, conversation killer.

40:36.100 --> 40:37.351
He got sick.

40:37.810 --> 40:38.978
And they, um...

40:40.062 --> 40:41.564
they tried to figure it out.

40:42.982 --> 40:44.859
But... they did not.

40:47.987 --> 40:50.531
-Love, I'm so sorry.
-No.

40:51.323 --> 40:52.408
No, it's...

40:58.789 --> 40:59.832
It is what it is.

41:01.167 --> 41:02.501
It was almost two years ago now.

41:02.585 --> 41:03.669
And, like, look...

41:04.420 --> 41:05.588
my life's great.

41:06.589 --> 41:08.340
And also, nobody really understands.

41:08.591 --> 41:10.759
I mean, who our age gets married,
let alone widowed?

41:11.635 --> 41:12.636
It's, like...

41:13.804 --> 41:14.805
Victorian.

41:16.932 --> 41:18.934
So, you know, people are nice, but...

41:20.519 --> 41:22.646
they can't really fathom
what I'm going through.

41:25.483 --> 41:26.650
Yeah, it's lonely.

41:27.735 --> 41:28.944
I can imagine.

41:30.738 --> 41:31.655
Yeah, I know.

41:32.740 --> 41:35.701
Ever since it happened, I've been able
to see this thing in people...

41:37.161 --> 41:38.370
who've been through it.

41:40.247 --> 41:42.208
I see that every time I look in your eyes.

41:45.085 --> 41:45.920
Yeah.

41:46.879 --> 41:47.922
You've felt it.

41:51.300 --> 41:52.301
Real love.

41:54.887 --> 41:55.888
Real loss.

41:58.516 --> 41:59.391
Yeah.

42:07.483 --> 42:09.193
Yeah, well...

42:09.777 --> 42:10.986
Did you fall in love?

42:12.029 --> 42:12.988
LA?

42:13.697 --> 42:14.907
Is it so terrible?

42:17.743 --> 42:18.869
It's not terrible.

42:20.829 --> 42:21.705
Good.

42:26.794 --> 42:28.546
I, uh, I got you a, um...

42:30.297 --> 42:31.590
a parting gift.

42:37.012 --> 42:39.223
Yeah, I thought about getting you
something happy, but...

42:39.723 --> 42:40.849
<i> Of course.</i>

42:41.141 --> 42:43.227
<i>-Joan Didion.</i>
- Let's face it,

42:43.310 --> 42:45.396
what you're more interested in
is something...

42:45.938 --> 42:48.148
smart and complex.

42:49.441 --> 42:50.776
A little... dark.

42:51.735 --> 42:52.611
Right?

42:53.779 --> 42:55.239
That's what makes you feel at home.

42:55.531 --> 42:56.740
How do you know that?

42:58.576 --> 42:59.577
Well, 'cause...

43:00.160 --> 43:01.078
me too.

43:03.998 --> 43:06.500
<i> I wanted to think you don't know me.</i>

43:07.376 --> 43:11.005
<i>You can't, but I'm not too proud</i>
<i>to say when I'm wrong.</i>

43:11.380 --> 43:14.008
<i>And maybe I was wrong about you,</i>

43:14.341 --> 43:17.678
<i>and maybe, even a bit, all of LA.</i>

43:17.761 --> 43:22.141
<i>And all I can say is,</i>
<i>I hope I'm also wrong about me.</i>

43:22.224 --> 43:24.435
<i>Maybe I don't need to shut down forever.</i>

43:24.518 --> 43:27.187
<i>Maybe I don't need to run away so fast.</i>

43:27.813 --> 43:29.315
<i>And if that could be...</i>

43:29.690 --> 43:30.733
<i>with you...</i>

43:31.317 --> 43:32.234
Blow.

43:32.318 --> 43:33.235
Ellie.

43:33.319 --> 43:35.487
God, it's from <i>The Big Lebowski.</i>

43:35.821 --> 43:36.780
It's going on your list.

43:36.864 --> 43:38.532
It's two a.m. Does your sister--

43:38.616 --> 43:40.075
Oh, shut up, Dad.

43:40.868 --> 43:41.952
She's right inside.

43:42.369 --> 43:43.704
I just have insomnia.

43:44.663 --> 43:46.790
From the 14 Frappuccinos.

43:46.874 --> 43:48.667
Okay, sorry. I just wanna make sure--

43:48.751 --> 43:50.961
Okay, Mr. Rogers, good night.

43:51.045 --> 43:51.920
Good night.

43:53.297 --> 43:54.256
Oh, Will,

43:54.340 --> 43:56.342
someone came by looking for you.

43:57.092 --> 43:58.010
Old friend?

44:00.012 --> 44:02.306
Jesse. No, Jasper.

44:02.389 --> 44:05.184
He said that you had something
that you wanted to give back

44:05.267 --> 44:06.644
and that he'll be by.

44:07.186 --> 44:08.729
-<i> Fuck.</i>
-Thanks.

44:08.979 --> 44:11.273
Honestly, he seemed a little creepy.

44:12.941 --> 44:16.236
What can I say, friend?
I have creepy taste in friends.

44:16.779 --> 44:18.030
Ew!

45:39.820 --> 45:41.029
Who is Jasper?

45:43.073 --> 45:44.783
Why is he looking for you...

45:45.367 --> 45:46.326
Will?

45:47.536 --> 45:49.580
How are we gonna take care
of this problem?

45:51.290 --> 45:53.542
<i> So here's the thing, Love.</i>

45:53.625 --> 45:54.626
Cut!

45:55.002 --> 45:56.754
<i> It wasn't easy for me to get here,</i>

45:56.837 --> 45:58.964
<i>to buy myself a little time,</i>

45:59.047 --> 46:01.800
<i>this slim chance at a new life.</i>

46:03.552 --> 46:04.511
<i>And then...</i>

46:05.471 --> 46:06.722
<i>I saw you.</i>

46:08.557 --> 46:12.144
<i>And, you know, I really do believe</i>
<i>that things happen for a reason,</i>

46:12.227 --> 46:14.563
<i>that all the hard stuff and the craziness,</i>

46:14.646 --> 46:16.148
<i>and frankly, my own mistakes...</i>

46:16.815 --> 46:19.151
<i>they maybe all led me here...</i>

46:20.027 --> 46:21.236
<i>for a reason.</i>

46:21.987 --> 46:23.071
<i>At least I hope...</i>

46:23.739 --> 46:24.573
<i>that's true.</i>

46:24.656 --> 46:27.868
<i>Because I'm working as hard as I can</i>
<i>to make a fresh start here.</i>

46:27.951 --> 46:30.996
-What the hell were you thinking, Calvin?
-Ray said to stock more fiction.

46:31.079 --> 46:33.290
Yeah, he meant fiction
that people actually wanna read.

46:33.373 --> 46:34.958
- Okay, I just figured that--
-What?

46:35.417 --> 46:37.795
There's a human alive
who wants to read <i>Crime and Punishment?</i>

46:38.420 --> 46:41.298
Look, dude, find a way to move these

46:41.381 --> 46:43.759
or, uh... <i>something's </i>moving.

46:44.635 --> 46:45.886
<i> It's delicate,</i>

46:46.470 --> 46:48.305
<i>the whole... thing.</i>

46:48.388 --> 46:50.724
<i> I have this vacancy</i>
<i>on the first floor.</i>

46:50.808 --> 46:52.059
<i> I like the second floor.</i>

46:52.893 --> 46:54.728
<i> 'Cause it's not just a new home.</i>

46:56.188 --> 46:57.981
<i>It's a new me.</i>

47:08.116 --> 47:09.660
<i> I live right in the neighborhood.</i>

47:09.743 --> 47:10.619
<i>Kismet, right?</i>

47:10.702 --> 47:12.287
<i>I mean, what are the chances?</i>

47:12.371 --> 47:14.248
<i></i>
<i>And when something like that happens,</i>

47:14.331 --> 47:15.290
<i>when it's right,</i>

47:15.374 --> 47:19.753
<i>you start to feel everything aligning,</i>
<i>like fate saying yes.</i>

47:20.128 --> 47:22.005
<i>But again, delicate.</i>

47:22.631 --> 47:24.842
<i>Anyway, this is a bad time,</i>
<i>the worst time,</i>

47:24.925 --> 47:26.468
<i>for a complication.</i>

47:28.053 --> 47:30.514
<i>Maybe I should run right now, Love.</i>

47:31.932 --> 47:34.226
<i>But now I don't want to.</i>

47:34.852 --> 47:38.105
<i>I need to figure out a way</i>
<i>to see this through,</i>

47:38.564 --> 47:39.606
<i>whatever it is...</i>

47:41.400 --> 47:42.317
<i>with you.</i>

48:02.337 --> 48:04.047
<i>You win, Love.</i>

48:04.882 --> 48:05.924
<i>I'll stay.</i>

49:06.568 --> 49:08.820
Subtitle by Matheus Modesto
